name: Latitude: Ninety!

description:
Story #1 - The Sacred Cat of Set

Story #2 - The Pharaoh Will Rule Again

Story #3 - Out of the Tomb

Story #4 - The Ghostly Wonderer
Roachmill loses his cool as the "Laser Killer" stalks Roachmill's ex-wife! This is the third installment of a four-part epic that reveals the darker side of the four-armed exterminator.
Indicia incorrectly reads January, 1989.

Roachmillhas a new girl in his life- aPlayboycenterfold no less! Her measurements: 60-15-45 (what do you expect- she weighs two tons!), and her "turn-ons" include destroying buildings with a single blow, killing innocent bystanders, causing general panic and mayhem-- and eating her boyfriends! So, take a guess who's next on her menu!

Overview

Rally's frantic hunt for an antidote to the poison in her veins has led her straight to Goldie. Rally's so drugged out, she can't fight off the Italian hit woman and drug dealer. And, to make matters worse, she soon discovers that Goldie's hideout is home to a bevy of young women she has kidnapped, drugged, and brainwashed to use as her personal slaves and assassins!
name: Psychedelic

description:
Overview

Trapped in Goldie's hideout, Rally does her best to resist the hypnotic power of Goldie's Kerasine injections. In the meantime, Minnie-May searches for answers from an old medicine woman in Chinatown and Misty discovers Goldie's true intentions: to have Rally, in her hypnotized state, kill her old friend and Chicago detective, Roy Coleman!
name: Roy

description:
Rally seems to think she's got a way to break Goldie's hypnotic hold over her. Let's hope it works, because Rally's on her way to see Roy!
Save Roy by killing him! Those are the orders a brainwashed Rally Vincent got from Goldie. But the Italian hit woman isn't the only person who can make hypnotic suggestions. For Rally, the cold, firm touch of her CZ75's trigger is the key to wake her from her trance, and just in time. Now Roy's safe and sound, but Rally's a fugitive. The cops are on her tail for attacking a fellow police officer, and she's got a very important date in a graveyard!
name: Hammer Release

description:
Rally was able to break her hypnosis just long enough to barely shoot Roy, instead of outright killing him. Good for Roy but still not so good for Rally; she's now wanted by Chicago's finest as a wannabe cop killer and Goldie's still on the loose and Misty's her captive! Fortunately, May showed up just in time to keep Rally from getting hauled in.

Rally and May have caught Goldie by surprise. But the Italian hit woman still has an ace up her sleeve -- she can reactivate the post-hypnotic suggestions she planted in Rally's brain. When Goldie commands Rally not to shoot her, it's up to May and Becky to keep off the murderous Goldie and her gang of thugs long enough for Rally to recover her free will.
name: Poison of the Scorpion

description:
Becky arrives at the cemetery just in time to take advantage of Rally's hypnotic state. Using her own post-hypnotic suggestions, Becky gives Rally the directive to take Goldie down once and for all!
Can't Goldie be stopped? High on cocaine, and protected in bullet-proof clothing, the Mafia hit woman takes all of Becky's revolver rounds and all but Rally's last shot, and she keeps on coming!
name: Lost Game

description:
Who would have thought that Bean Bandit would show up to rescue Goldie! Does this mean that the sadistic ubervillainness has beaten our dear Rally?
Rally Vincent wishes it was all a bad dream. When she regains consciousness in a hospital bed, she discovers that not only has Goldie escaped, but Rally is under arrest for trying to kill Roy, and Misty is still Goldie's captive. To top it off, Goldie is going to pull the dirtiest trick of all: offering a court witness to clear Rally's name and put her in debt to the Mafia hit woman for getting her off!
name: Cool Down

description:
Overview

Rally Vincent is in a funk! The Chicago PD has revoked her bounty hunter license, she's not allowed to even carry a gun, and her doctor says she should give up "cause girls shouldn't do such nasty work anyway"! When even her friends are unsympathetic, she decides to track down the source of her present problems: Bean Bandit -- the getaway driver extraordinaire who snatched Goldie the assassin out from under Rally's nose. But Bean doesn't have the reputation for being the best for nothing; Rally's got her work cut out for her if she's going to try to capture "Rolling Bean"!
name: Rolling Bean

description:
Overview

Bean Bandit has taken on Rally's challenge -- if she can stop his latest drug delivery, it will be the last time he dabbles in the drug trade at all. With the help of cat burglar Misty, Rally has no problem sneaking into Bean's secret hideout. But what would happen if Bean walked through the door?

Overview

Save Roy by killing him! Those are the orders a brainwashed Rally Vincent got from Goldie. But the Italian hit woman isn't the only person who can make hypnotic suggestions. For Rally, the cold, firm touch of her CZ75's trigger is the key to wake her from her trance, and just in time. Now Roy's safe and sound, but Rally's a fugitive. The cops are on her tail for attacking a fellow police officer, and she's got a very important date in a graveyard!

Overview

The race is on! It's Rally's, well Rally's "borrowed" supercar against star drivers Bean Bandit and Riff Raff. The road is bad enough when you're trying to pass trucks and pedestrians at 150 miles an hour in the middle of the night. But add in snow, sharp curves, and a deadly assault rifle -- and the word "deathmatch" takes on a whole new meaning!

Overview

Can't Goldie be stopped? High on cocaine, and protected in bullet-proof clothing, the Mafia hit woman takes all of Becky's revolver rounds and all but Rally's last shot, and she keeps on coming!

Bean shot! What next?! No one, no matter how bulletproof, not even Bean, could survive a point-blank shot like the one Jones delivered, could he?
Friends or foes? Rally may have saved Bean's life in his showdown with the double-crossing drug dealer Jones. But as far as Chicago's #1 underworld driver is concerned, beating Rally's efforts to get him out of drug running is almost as important as getting his load of drugs to New York on time.
name: Missing Washington

description:
Overview

Dangerous liaisons! The mafia information source Bean has an appointment to see is waiting for him with three heavily armed goons. But that's nothing compared to the hotel where Minnie-May is waiting to meet Rally. Over there, room service shows up with silencers and laser-sight assassin pistols. There's something rotten in the Big Apple, and Rally Vincent's about to walk right into the middle of it!

Overview

It's the perfect trap. Until a hapless Mafia assassin finds herself up against Rally Vincent! It's a perfect plan. Until Bean shows up at Jones's rendezvous instead of his hired bodyguard! The best-laid plans of mice and men will often go astray, especially when they run into Rally Vincent and Bean Bandit. Now can the two of them stop the biggest setup of all--the hardcore drug deal for 100 kilograms of potent Kerasene?!

Overview

When Bean crashes the drug deal between Jones and the New York Mafia, he has to prove that the ex-boxer Jones has brought along isn't the real Road Buster. And Rally, armed with just four bullets, has to decide whether or not to step in and help him. Sometimes the only answer comes from the barrel of a gun, or from a pair of trained fists!

Overview

It's a pretty normal job for Chicago's hottest bounty hunter, Rally Vincent and her sidekick Minnie-May: stake out the house of television magician Mr. Smart, who jumped bail after a traffic accident. Maybe if Rally hadn't been having all these dreams about her missing father whom she loved and whom her mother had hated, she'd be feeling fine. But when it turns out that Smart's wife has set him up with the help of her conniving lawyer-lover, things start getting messy.

Overview

Rally is used to thinking of herself as a good guy. After all, as a bounty hunter, she brings in people who've jumped bail to escape the law. But try explaining that to Tom, Flora, and Agnes, three friends of Mr. Smart's daughter Jeena who are sure Rally is after an innocent man. It looks like the story of Mr. Smart's divorce and jumping bail is not as clear as it all seemed--and that Jeena's mother may have set up her magician husband for a fall.

Overview

When Rally winds up in charge of Mr. Smart's daughter, a blackmail hostage with an explosive necklace locked around her neck, an already complicated case turns downright insane. Can Ken disarm the necklace before it's too late? Can Rally find out why one of the world's most famous magicians is cooperating with a bunch of underworld hoods? What's a bounty hunter to do?

Overview

Rally has finally persuaded Jeena's friends that she's one of the good guys. But now it's a race against time to stop the bad guys from pulling off a heist that could leave Mister Smart on the run for his life, and possibly cost Jeena her own!

Overview

How good a hypnotist is Mr. Smart? Good enough to get Brose the mafia driver to betray his own godfather! Right on cue, the young mafia driver starts unloading the drugs, while the 50-caliber bullets of Sharko's Desert Eagle keep the godfather and his bodyguards in check. But what neither set of gangsters knows is that Rally Vincent has been tailing them, waiting for her chance. While Ken races against time to dismantle Jeena's explosive collar, Rally and Misty race against a different kind of enemy: Cobra versus Hummer in the middle of the night!

Overview

The race is on! As Riff-Raff pilots the heist team's Hummer through snow-shrouded forests on the outskirts of Chicago, Rally is flooring it on the snow-slick roadways to head her off on the other side! Can Rally's high-speed "long cut" around the forest keep her on the bad guy's tail? And how can they get word to Mister Smart inside the Hummer that his daughter Jeena is safe and he no longer has to cooperate with her captors?

Overview

Rally's been hit by a .50-caliber round from a Desert Eagle -- but the battle's not over yet! And things haven't been going so well in the Hummer, either: the kidnappers' leader has just revealed that he's in disguise, and he's going to kill them all after they get away with the money! But Rally's ready to counterattack -- and it's showdown time!

Overview

The bad guy has a grenade launcher. Rally has a handgun -- and broken ribs. How can she possibly turn the tables? By remembering the advice of the best teacher she ever had -- her long-lost father. She's only got one chance before the pain from her ribs destroys her aim, and she has to make it count!

Overview

It's a family affair! When little Flora comes to after her abduction, she finds she's back in Jeena's house, and Jeena's mom has an explosive collar around her neck, just like her daughter! Jeena's mom asks Flora not to run away, in case the man who kidnapped her kills them all. But he's downstairs at that very moment, and if someone doesn't stop him, he's going to make a clean getaway -- with the stolen Mafia money!

Overview

The criminal ringleader Mr. Borgnine has Flora, Tom, and Agnes in the sights of his shotgun, and there's no way that Rally can stop him from getting off one shot. And Mr. Smart is looking down the barrel of his ex-wife Deborah's handgun. It's Rally versus a man with no conscience, and Mr. Smart versus an old love. Can Borgnine be stopped, and Deborah brought back to her senses, before this family's "home sweet home" turns into a slaughterhouse? Don't miss this miniseries' stunning conclusion!

This issue contains the following stories:

Conflict - Amid the fiery action in Viet-Nam, an older more deadly clash emerges.

How it Began - A brief look into the days when aerial combat took wing.

The Edge - What makes the crucial difference as jet fighters duel in Korea's skies?

Give and Take - Join the see-saw battle for a hilltop in World War II Italy.

ME-262 - The amazing facts behind the plane that could have won the war for Hitler.

The Trench - Mud and death await a night patrol into no man's land.

Thermopylae - One of the most heroic stands in the history of warfare.

Night Drop - Paratroopers jump into the waiting guns of the S.S.
